Subject: [liste-egc] Appel: Call for participation, CLEF MC2 Evaluation Lab
 2018 (Task 1: Cross Language cultural microblog search)

(apologies for multiple postings)

CLEF MC2 : Multilingual Cultural Mining and Retrieval Evaluation Lab
2018 – Task 1: Cross Language cultural microblog search

https://mc2.talne.eu/spip/tasks-2018/1-cross-language-culture-microblog-search/

Lab registration now open at
http://clef2018-labs-registration.dei.unipd.it/

Held as part of CLEF 2018 Conference and Labs on the Evaluation Forum
Information Access Evaluation meets Multilinguality, Multimodality and
Visualization

10 - 14 September 2018, Avignon – France

Browsing the VodKaster website allows French reader to get personal 
short comments called (microcritics) about movies. You can get similar 
and/or complementary opinions on twitter but they are quite less 
specific to movies and then harder to find.  The use case is to display 
to the reader a concise summary of microblogs related to the 
microcritics he/she is reading considering bilingual and trilingual 
users that would read microblogs in other languages then French.

The Task 1 of MC2 CLEF Lab deals with Cross Language cultural microblog 
retrieval issue. It aims to automatically identify microblogs related to 
the topics and/or opinions expressed within VodKaster microcritics'. The 
objective is to provide users with direct access to related 
argumentative microblogs. In this task, relevant information is 
expressed in the form of a readable summary composed of related 
microblogs about a given topic.

Given a movie title and microcritics from the French VodKaster Social 
Network, find all relevant microblogs from MC2 corpus in French, 
English, Spanish, Portuguese and Arabic. Runs will be evaluated based on 
the informativity of top ranked microblogs which combines graded 
relevance scores and diversity following INEX Tweets Contextualisation 
methodology and using the FRESA software extended to Arabic, French, 
Portuguse and spanish. All FRESA metrics will be computed between runs 
top ranked microblog extracts and a textual reference to be provided by 
organizers. This reference will be based on both manual and pools runs 
from participant submissions.

Please see
https://mc2.talne.eu/spip/tasks-2018/1-cross-language-culture-microblog-search/ 
for
full details about the task 1.

And register at http://clef2018-labs-registration.dei.unipd.it

We strongly encourage everyone involved in information retrieval, text 
mining, natural language processing, machine learning and social 
networks analysis to participate.

